<exercise id="fs-idm174365776">
<problem id="fs-idm97516528">
<para id="fs-idm122332368">Write the symbol for each of the following ions:</para>
<para id="fs-idp77154592">(a) the ion with a 1+ charge, atomic number 55, and mass number 133</para>
<para id="fs-idm125607744">(b) the ion with 54 electrons, 53 protons, and 74 neutrons</para>
<para id="fs-idm91510448">(c) the ion with atomic number 15, mass number 31, and a 3− charge</para>
<para id="fs-idm78032064">(d) the ion with 24 electrons, 30 neutrons, and a 3+ charge</para>
</problem>
<solution id="fs-idm78148384">
<para id="fs-idm90412768">(a) <sup>133</sup>Cs<sup>+</sup>; (b) <sup>127</sup>I<sup>−</sup>; (c) <sup>31</sup>P<sup>3−</sup>; (d) <sup>57</sup>Co<sup>3+</sup></para>
</solution>
</exercise>
